        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 1:30PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 130 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Barre City, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Barre, Montpelier, Barre Town, Plainfield, Northfield Village,
Northfield, Websterville, East Montpelier, Barre City, Berlin,
Williamstown, E F Knapp State Airport, Middlesex, Washington,
Marshfield, Calais, Orange, Moretown, Riverton, and West Berlin.

This includes Interstate 89 between mile markers 44 and 56.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
